Show porjection of inserion sites into a latent space

ggplot(df, aes(x=X, y=Y, color=Response_class)) +
  geom_point()

ggplot(df, aes(x=X, y=Y, color=Response_class)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap( ~ Response_class)

Formatting projection and responce of each site

pyx <- df %>% select(c(X,Y))
pyy <- df %>% select(Response_class)

3 Running python code

The “r” object python contains an interface to the R variables

import pandas
from sklearn.neighbors import RadiusNeighborsClassifier

model = RadiusNeighborsClassifier(radius=0.1)
__ = model.fit(r.pyx,r.pyy.values.ravel())
yhat = model.predict(r.pyx)

The “py” object in R contains an interface to the python variables

df_imp1 <- df[py$yhat == df$Response_class,]

 ggplot(df_imp1, aes(x=X, y=Y,color=Response_class)) +
 geom_point() +
 facet_wrap( ~ Response_class)

More information can be found in https://rstudio.github.io/reticulate/
